\begin{chessboard}
[fen]rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR
\end{chessboard}

\end{document}
```

This code uses the `chessboard` package to draw a chessboard. The `[fen]` option specifies that the board should be drawn using Forsyth-Edwards Notation (FEN). The FEN string `rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR` represents the starting position of a chess game.

The `\begin{chessboard}` and `\end{chessboard}` commands mark the beginning and end of the chessboard environment. The `[fen]` option is placed inside the square brackets after the `\begin{chessboard}` command.

The chessboard will be drawn using the default settings of the `chessboard` package. These settings can be customized using various options. For example, the `squaresize` option can be used to specify the size of the squares in the chessboard.

Here is an example of a more customized chessboard:

```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}

\begin{document}

\begin{chessboard}[squaresize=2cm, style=modern, showcoordinates=true]
[fen]rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR
\end{chessboard}

\end{document}
```

This code produces a chessboard with a square size of 2cm, a modern style, and the coordinates of the squares are shown.

